					<head>Mishnah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n80017842" rend="visible">
						<summary>A large portion of Maimonides' Commentary on Seder Zera῾im in Judeo-Arabic, preceded by a fragment belonging to an anonymous Arabic commentary in the form of questions and answers on the Mishneh Torah of the same author.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="jrb-Hebr"/>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n80017842">
							<locus from="1r" to="138v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush Seder zera῾im</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש סדר זרעים</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495" xml:lang="en">Maimonides, Moses, 1135-1204</persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/100185495" xml:lang="he">משה בן מימון, 1138-1204 </persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>The fragments of the Arabic commentary on Maimonides' Mishneh Torah extends from the end of chapter two in Ḳeriʾat shema῾ to the beginning of chapter thirteen in Hilkhot tefilah, followed by a smaller fragment of the same commentary on Hilkhot shevitat yom ṭov, extending from the latter part of chapter one to the beginning of chapter five.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
